The `DashboardLayout` component serves as the primary layout for the application's dashboard section. It establishes a two-column structure, featuring a sidebar on the left and the main content area on the right.

## Purpose

This layout component is responsible for the overall structure and common elements of all pages within the `/dashboard` route. It ensures a consistent navigation experience with the `Sidebar` and provides a dedicated space for the main page content.

## Key Exports

- **`DashboardLayout`**: A React functional component.

## Props

- **`children`**: `React.ReactNode` - The content of the page that will be rendered within the main content area of the layout.

## Usage

This layout is automatically applied to any component rendered under the `/dashboard` route when using Next.js's App Router convention.

```tsx
// Example of a page that would use this layout:
// app/dashboard/page.tsx

import React from 'react';

export default function DashboardHomePage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Welcome to your Dashboard</h1>
      <p>This is the main content area.</p>
    </div>
  );
}

// The layout.tsx file in app/dashboard will wrap this page's content.
```

## Structure

The component renders a main `div` with flexbox properties to arrange the `Sidebar` and the main content horizontally. The `Sidebar` occupies a fixed width, while the `main` content area takes up the remaining space and allows for vertical scrolling if its content exceeds the viewport height. The `bg-background` class sets the background color, and `overflow-hidden` on the outer container prevents scrollbars from appearing on the main layout wrapper.
